    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-10-24T21:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-10-24T21:00:00-05:00" n="820"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">856A.20/55a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to The
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-10-24T21:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 24, 1941—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1012. From the Under Secretary.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>Ambassador Biddle has informed us that an invitation in the sense
                        mentioned in my 940, October 13, 9 p.m., is being sent by the Netherlands
                        Government to the Brazilian Government through the Netherlands Minister at
                        Rio de Janeiro. Please telegraph when the invitation has been
                        received.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>The text of the joint United States–Netherlands statement regarding
                        Surinam which is to be issued will be telegraphed to you as soon as it shall
                        have been agreed upon. [Welles.]</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
